{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"A\n    \n      Minimal — Environment-Driven\n      YAML just declares the provider type. Everything else from az login context or env vars.\n      \n        Python\n        \nazure = ast.Provider(name=\"azure\", type=\"azure-container-apps\")\n\nagent = ast.Agent(\n    name=\"support-bot\",\n    model=model,\n    channels=[ast.Channel(name=\"api\", type=ast.ChannelType.API)],\n    resources=[ast.Resource(name=\"sessions\", provider=azure, engine=\"postgres\")],\n)\n# Region, subscription, RG all come from:\n#   az login context, or\n#   AZURE_SUBSCRIPTION_ID, AZURE_LOCATION, AZURE_RESOURCE_GROUP\n        \n      \n      \n        YAML\n        \nname: support-bot\nresources:\n  - name: sessions\n    provider:\n      name: azure\n      type: azure-container-apps\n    engine: postgres","choice":"a","id":null,"timestamp":1776039941604}
