{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"A\n    \n      Typed resource classes\n      Each resource type is its own class. Explicit, discoverable, IDE-friendly.\n      \n        Python\n        \nagent = ast.Agent(\n    name=\"support-bot\",\n    model=model,\n    platform=ast.Platform(type=\"container-apps\", provider=azure),\n    session_store=ast.PostgresStore(provider=azure),\n    memory_store=ast.PostgresStore(\n        provider=azure,\n        config={\"sku\": \"Standard_B1ms\"},\n    ),\n)\n\n# Or bring your own:\nagent = ast.Agent(\n    ...\n    session_store=ast.PostgresStore(\n        connection_string_env=\"DATABASE_URL\",\n    ),\n)\n        \n      \n      Clear what each thing is. No engine=\"postgres\" string. Type-safe config per store type.","choice":"a","id":null,"timestamp":1776042393909}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"A\n    \n      Typed resource classes\n      Each resource type is its own class. Explicit, discoverable, IDE-friendly.\n      \n        Python\n        \nagent = ast.Agent(\n    name=\"support-bot\",\n    model=model,\n    platform=ast.Platform(type=\"container-apps\", provider=azure),\n    session_store=ast.PostgresStore(provider=azure),\n    memory_store=ast.PostgresStore(\n        provider=azure,\n        config={\"sku\": \"Standard_B1ms\"},\n    ),\n)\n\n# Or bring your own:\nagent = ast.Agent(\n    ...\n    session_store=ast.PostgresStore(\n        connection_string_env=\"DATABASE_URL\",\n    ),\n)\n        \n      \n      Clear what each thing is. No engine=\"postgres\" string. Type-safe config per store type.","choice":"a","id":null,"timestamp":1776042435293}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"B\n    \n      Named fields on Agent, generic Store\n      Agent has explicit fields for each concern. One Store class handles backing config.\n      \n        Python\n        \nagent = ast.Agent(\n    name=\"support-bot\",\n    model=model,\n    platform=ast.Platform(type=\"container-apps\", provider=azure),\n    sessions=ast.Store(engine=\"postgres\", provider=azure),\n    memory=ast.Store(engine=\"postgres\", provider=azure, config={\n        \"sku\": \"Standard_B1ms\",\n    }),\n)\n\n# Bring your own:\nagent = ast.Agent(\n    ...\n    sessions=ast.Store(\n        engine=\"postgres\",\n        connection_string_env=\"DATABASE_URL\",\n    ),\n)\n        \n      \n      Agent shape is clear (sessions, memory are named fields). Store is flexible but still generic.","choice":"b","id":null,"timestamp":1776042447914}
